==English==

===Etymology===
Arbitrary letters + -on (by analagy with cotton)

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪlɒn|-aɪlɒn]]

====Noun====
{{wikipedia}}
'''nylon'''
#Originally, the [[DuPont]] company trade name for [[polyamide]], a [[copolymer]] whose molecules consist of alternating diamine and dicarboxylic acid [[monomer]]s bonded together.  This word has come to be generically used for this type of [[polymer]]
{{en-noun}}
#(''especially in plural'') A women's [[stocking]] originally fabricated from nylon.  Generically, it has come to mean any women's long, sheer stocking.

